{
  "text": "Bus operations, during provision of their service, interact with three main agents: bus agent, passenger agent and traffic agent [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Bus networks characteristics include several components: system performance and level of service (Vuchic, 1981; [CITATION_3] . Bus service may be of one type or a combination of them, such as: local, express, feeder and commuter [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Bus service performance measurement is based on unit departures per hour (Vuchic, 1981) . This is achieved through the valuationof the following parameters [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
